data.name: checkBoxModiconFloat.ToolTip
data.value:
Check this if Modicon Float is used. The least significant bytes are sent in the first register and the most significant bytes in the second register.
It will automatically decode the message when this checkbox is clicked.

data.name: radioButtonSlave.ToolTip
data.value:
This is used to determine if a transmitted (TX) or received (RX) message is a request or a respons. This is needed to decode the Modbus message properly
A Slave that transmitts (TX) is responding A Slave receives (RX) a request

data.name: radioButtonMaster.ToolTip
data.value:
This is used to determine if a transmitted (TX) or received (RX) message is a request or a respons. This is needed to decode the Modbus message properly
A Master that transmitts (TX) is requesting A Master receives (RX) a response
